How to import in eclipse:

1) install gradle http://www.gradle.org/downloads
2) run: gradle eclipse
3) start eclipse
4) File -> Import -> Existing Projects into Workspace
5) select participact-server
6) right click on the project and choose Configure -> Convert to Gradle Project

================

Set up Tomcat:

1) Add a Charset Encoding filter to support UTF-8: edit web.xml of tomcat (v7.x)
   and add the following filter as *first* filter:
    <filter>
        <filter-name>CharacterEncodingFilter</filter-name>
        <filter-class>org.apache.catalina.filters.SetCharacterEncodingFilter</filter-class>
        <init-param>
            <param-name>encoding</param-name>
            <param-value>UTF-8</param-value>
        </init-param>
    </filter>

    <filter-mapping>
        <filter-name>CharacterEncodingFilter</filter-name>
        <url-pattern>/*</url-pattern>
    </filter-mapping>
    
2) Edit the Connector to interpret URIs as UTF-8:
    <Connector URIEncoding="UTF-8" connectionTimeout="20000" port="8080" protocol="HTTP/1.1" redirectPort="8443"/>

================

When use this application in your publications, please cite:
 - ParticipAct: A Large-Scale Crowdsensing Platform (http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/7111277/) 
 - Mobile crowd sensing management with the ParticipAct living lab (https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1574119216302127)
 